    "As a rule, applying filtering every 20 -50 iterations produces stable simulations maintaining physical gradients and diminishing noise in the solution.",
    "Finally, it is interesting to note that the filtering fits perfectly the concept of split variables.",
    "According to Hesthaven (1998), a high-frequency noise filtering can improve the long-time stability of the PML, see Section 3.7.",
    "In MANCHA3D this approach is shown to work successfully for simulations of MHD waves.",
    "In MANCHA3D no specific treatment is applied to control the divergence of the magnetic field."
